            }
        }
        Err(e) => eprintln!("Error: {}", e),
    }
}
```
The ? operator propagates errors up the call stack — if read_to_string fails, the function returns Err immediately. entry().or_insert(0) inserts a default value if the key is absent, then returns a mutable reference to the value regardless. sort_by with b.cmp(a) gives descending order.

