    for _ in 0..6 {
        println!("{:?} ({} sec) go={}", light, light.duration_secs(), light.can_go());
        light = light.next();
    }
}
```
Rust enums are algebraic data types — variants can hold data. match is exhaustive: every variant must be handled or the code won't compile. matches!() is a macro that returns true if the value matches the pattern.

